+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01PTZgiPsCd8AKnWQG3PMv6R","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good. I have a clear picture of the project. This is a non-interactive environment, so I'll use Autopilot mode. The problem is well-specified — both functions require Gaussian elimination over GF(2) (for toggle) and GF(p) (for counter). Let me design and go straight to implementation.\n\n**Non-interactive mode: using Autopilot.**\n\nThe design is straightforward — this is a classic linear algebra over finite fields problem:\n\n1. **solveToggle**: System of linear equations over GF(2). Each button is a variable (0 or 1), each light gives an equation. Use Gaussian elimination over GF(2), then enumerate free variables to find the minimum-press, lexicographically smallest solution.\n\n2. **solveCounter**: System of linear equations over GF(p) where p is prime. Each button pressed 0 to p-1 times. Gaussian elimination over GF(p), then enumerate free variables to minimize total presses with lex-smallest tiebreaker.\n\nThis design is determined by the math — no real alternatives to explore. Let me proceed directly to implementation via TDD."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1504,"cache_read_input_tokens":23343,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1504},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bf2fdf11-6c0f-47cc-ae89-6f655ede872a","uuid":"53f80d5b-489c-474f-ac3c-dd2f3b893238"}
